---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Now | Jevan Cousins"
  description="What Jevan Cousins is working on now, as of April 2026."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-display font-bold mb-2">Now</h1>
    <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-8">Last updated: April 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        <strong>Finishing at AllianzGI.</strong> My last day is 28 February 2026. I spent four years building production systems for a global 176 billion euro Fixed Income platform: architecting the firm's first enterprise agentic AI system, leading the rollout of MSCI BarraOne performance attribution, and directing AI adoption across operations.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        <strong>Iterating on Lineup's data platform.</strong> Refactoring the Airflow pipeline into a maintainable Python package, adding data quality tests in dbt, and optimising the entity deduplication logic across six API sources. Planning analytics dashboards in Looker Studio for pipeline health monitoring.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        <strong>Extending NutriPlan.</strong> API now supports meal swapping, user feedback loops, and household meal coordination. iOS frontend design is complete; implementation underway with SwiftUI. Targeting a beta launch by summer.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        <strong>Job searching for applied AI roles.</strong> Targeting positions based in Paris or London focused on system architecture and AI-powered product development. Particularly interested in forward-deployed and solution architecture paths.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        <strong>Earnings Call Analyser research project.</strong> Exploring whether Q&A alignment in earnings call transcripts predicts forward equity returns (following Chiang et al. 2025). Building a PyTorch NLP pipeline with FinBERT embeddings and contrastive learning, with backtesting framework for validation. Proof of concept stage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
